definition: to finish work/to complete a project

sentences.english: Manny: Of course it's still work in progress. Few rough edges, here and there.
sentences.chinese: 當然了，這工程還沒完工還有些邊邊角角要處理。

sentences.english: Jin Mao Tower was completed in 1999 and is the fourth tallest building of the world.
sentences.chinese: 金茂大廈於1999年完工，是世界第四高的建築物。

sentences.english: The new railway station has been completed.
When completed , the museum will be open to the public next year.
sentences.chinese: 完工後，博物館將在明年向公衆開放。

sentences.english: When completed, the new railway will run for250miles.
sentences.chinese: 完工後，新的鐵路線將有250英里長。

sentences.english: With the impounding of Three Gorges Project, study on this problem became urgent.
sentences.chinese: 隨着三峽工程完工蓄水，這方面的研究顯得愈加迫切。
達濠，納粹第一個集中營，完工。

sentences.english: Check the joining su ces of the generator bearing after finishing the unit alignment.
sentences.chinese: 機組再對中完工後，檢查發電機軸承接合面良好。

sentences.english: We can't wait to see the episodes start to come to life.
sentences.chinese: 我們等不及要看到完工後的新劇集了。

sentences.english: The project was successfully completed in 1966.
sentences.chinese: 這項工程於1966年順利完工。

sentences.english: When the cofferdams are completed and made safe, the water trapped between them is pumped out.
sentences.chinese: 圍堰完工穩固後，就將圍堰間的水抽乾。

sentences.english: It is required for surveyor to check draft after completion of first batch of cargo.
sentences.chinese: 第一票貨完工後需要商檢看水尺，請做好準備。

sentences.english: Finally the Cross-stitch has been finished after almost one months hardworking.
sentences.chinese: 經過將近一個月的奮戰，我的十字繡作品終於完工了。

sentences.english: Factory finishes for steel frames are prime coated and must be finished on the job.
sentences.chinese: 鋼製架構的產品光漆是預先打上的，必須當場完工。

sentences.english: The never-completed toilets were gaping holes that had to be covered.
sentences.chinese: 未完工的廁所成了一個個大洞，必須填起來。

definition: to begin work (of a factory or engineering operation)/to start a construction job
to open to traffic (e.g. new bridge, rail line etc)/(of a locality) to have a transportation service/(Tw) to commute
time allocated for a project/completion date
construction/to carry out construction or large-scale repairs
to repair/to refurbish/to renovate/to refit/to mend/to rebuild
to join the two sections (of a linear structure: bridge, dike etc) to complete its construction
to complete the last stage of work/to round off
to lay (railroad tracks, carpet, pipeline)/to install (wiring, cable)/to construct (road, concrete slab)
